<TITLE> Ramadan begins Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com)Ramadan, the Muslim month of fasting and religious reflection, will begin on Sunday, according to a decision of the National Moon-sighting Committee. The Khatib of Baitul Mukarram national mosque, Mohammed Salauddin, a member of the committee, broke the news to reporters after the meeting on Friday night as the moon could not be seen anywhere in the country. The committee started its meeting chaired by its chairman state minister for religious affairs Shahjahan Miah at 8:15pm at the Islamic Foundation's conference room, an official preferring not to be named said. Considered as the holiest month in the Islamic year, Ramadan commemorates the time when the Qu'ran is said to have been revealed to the Prophet Muhammad. Ramadan ends when the first crescent of the new moon is sighted again, marking the beginning of the Eid-al-Fitr. bdnew
